e changes that we believe will greatly benefit our customer base.   <br><br><br>We have shifted the manner in which our In-Game Customer petitions and emails are handled and gone to more of a "global queue" approach.  There will no longer be a single Game Master present on each server.  Instead, teams of Game Masters will assist those servers with the greatest need and longest waiting times.  In addition, a dedicated team of Game Masters will also be responsible for answering In-Game email inquiries.  We are confident this change will grant an even higher level of Customer Support by providing faster response times while continuing to provide all of the dynamic quests and events you have come to expect. <br><br><br>Game Masters will continue to have a strong presence in Norrath, while providing greater customer satisfaction.  In fact, you will most likely see more of them on your server in the future.  <br><br><br>Thank you for your continued support."<br><br><br><br><br>Okay. I'm still sort of thinking about this right now. If a GM no longer has a "home" server, and they just float around from server to server... our petitions will take even LONGER to be answered. We'll now have to wait like 6 hours (oh wait, petitions decay after 3..) for a responce from a GM. You know when guides answer them and say "okay, GM soandso will be online tomorrow at 3pm PST. Petition then"... Now they'll have to say "Sorry, friend... I have no fvcking idea when a GM will be online. Petition non stop and *MAYBE* you'll get in contact with one eventually. Safe travels! *poof*" /sigh, Verant...... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukamakasibattlemaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kamakasi Battlemaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 395<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/02 11:58:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3407.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hrmm.. IMPROVED customer service from Verant?</span><hr size=1> It may help some. The way I think about it is that the servers with much lower amounts of Petitions and problems would have GM's and Guides in CS home much more often playing gems. By doing what they are doing, it is putting the petitions of other servers that would otherwise get delayed into the hands of GM's and Guides that are not doing anything. <br><br>One way to look at it, at least they are trying something different. <br><br>/shrug<br><br><br>Kama<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udwelfnvhal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DwelfnVhal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/02 4:06:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3407.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hrmm.. IMPROVED customer service from Verant?</span><hr size=1> If they had a floating pool to supplement the server GM's then I might be inclined to agree with you Kama. However....<br><br>Val <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/02 8:26:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3407.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td>